==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|detonāre}}. It meant "to stop thundering", e.g. as in weather (''de-'' = "from", ''tonare'' = "to thunder"). The current English meaning seems to be a new formation in postclassical times.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈdɛtəneɪt/|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|detonat}}

# {{label|en|intransitive}} To [[explode]]; to blow up. Specifically, to [[combust]] [[supersonic]]ally via [[shock]] [[compression]].
# {{label|en|transitive}} To cause an [[explosion]].

